abstract_ssm: Milly Itzhak was actively involved in the local art, music, DIY and youth activism scenes in Florida and created and published several zines between 92-96. During this time she maintained correspondence with youth and feminist activists and zine writers around the United States. The Collection consists primarily of zines either created by Itzhak or sent to Itzhak in the early and mid 1990s. There is also a small amount of associated correspondence and other ephemera that was sent through the mail.
